<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-94-0696 </DOCNO><TEXT>The book discusses problems arising in the field of tension between therequirements of statute law and those of radioactive waste management,particularly considering procedural law. The problems are dealt withon the basis of an assessment of the practical situation in comparablefields of law, as for instance and above all the law on the peacefulutilisation of nuclear energy. The survey also considers controversialopinions and statements concerning this explosive technology: Concernof citizens as well as the statements and knowledge of engineers, naturalscientists, legal experts, and politicians. Readers who are interestedin these topics, or involved in the matter, will find with this booka competent survey of current legal problems connected with radioactivewaste management and the legal protection offered by the law.</TEXT></DOC>